name: Escapism - Zine
description:
5th Edition to the Objekt series. 

This work is a hand-stitched, 30 page zine, documenting the underground of the city in an attempt to escape the mundane and the ordinary.

name: Objekt Issue 4
description:
Issue 4. Published to explore the idea of graffiti that exists on surfaces that move. The zine documents this vectorial world, with a focus on the scene within Sydney and Melbourne. Each example of this 'modern day palimpsest' has been redrawn and exhibited with a Gallery style citation - with the format itself effecting the essence of what is being shown.

Hand Stitched.

Price includes postage.

name: Objekt Issue 3
description: Outlines my design work, with key images from the realms of street photography, architecture, graphic design, film, and art. The work is limited edition with high print costs and high quality production. 22 full colour pages, all hand stitched.

name: Issue 2
description:
Following the concept of Free Form Jazz, this edition explores the way the essence of jazz manifests itself in certain moments throughout life and on the streets. It includes short stories written into the imagery that is displayed across 24 pages. The work follows a cinematic perspective through Sydney and Melbourne streets.

Hand Stitched

Price Includes Postage
